<subSubSection id="0F60EF9D64743A3AB0ADC681E1FEA551" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="notes">
<paragraph id="871BC874759A60E4D88AC389F0A21187" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="41E27F7D0750E851D0FDEA29EB385C12" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<bibRefCitation id="7C254175864D8154E8F847323099818D" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="INTA, Buenos Aires" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B34" refString="Philippi, RA, 1857. Plantarum novarum Chilensium: centuria quarta, quinta, sexta. Linnaea 29(1): 1-47, 48-95, 96-110." title="Plantarum novarum Chilensium: centuria quarta, quinta, sexta. Linnaea 29 (1): 1 - 47, 48 - 95, 96 - 110." year="1857">Rudolph A. Philippi (1857)</bibRefCitation>
based the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="6E7F75544F26916220EA8474411D7276" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium dimorphum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dimorphum">
<emphasis id="5DF9FCBDC79AA5E8241AF36D4621E1EC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium dimorphum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on a collection he made in Santiago, Chile, without explicit further reference to any locality. 
<bibRefCitation id="36CE4D80A8A8D35BBFD3C54249D3BF92" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, in his revision of 
<taxonomicName id="3BFF062B2CC85F8B350C0E1FABA14D2A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cryptantha" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87C8A6E1BC3BFB4D6618DA57F301A9EB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in South America, referred to a specimen lodged at SGO as the 
<normalizedToken id="CA6DD3328CC8F31BAAB90ABAE51A8EE9" originalValue="“type”">&quot;type&quot;</normalizedToken>
of the name. However, an additional duplicate annotated, in 
<normalizedToken id="B83FD1BEC56D4B672DD0ACBF2B9C7AB3" originalValue="Philippi’s">Philippi's</normalizedToken>
hand, as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="0C848F4C2EF2152F488AB8AD903DB909" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium dimorphum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dimorphum">Eritrichium dimorphum</taxonomicName>
&quot;, is found at CORD. Both specimens are in agreement with the diagnosis as referred to by 
<bibRefCitation id="57A09CA0E90B9B16EE734C7C497C84B4" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="INTA, Buenos Aires" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B34" refString="Philippi, RA, 1857. Plantarum novarum Chilensium: centuria quarta, quinta, sexta. Linnaea 29(1): 1-47, 48-95, 96-110." title="Plantarum novarum Chilensium: centuria quarta, quinta, sexta. Linnaea 29 (1): 1 - 47, 48 - 95, 96 - 110." year="1857">Philippi (1857)</bibRefCitation>
. Therefore, the element cited by Johnston and his statement must be considered as an effective lectotypification of the name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
